text: The JAC Binyue also known as JAC J7 is a mid-size car made by JAC Motors from 2008 to 2012. == History and Features == The JAC Binyue was launched in 2008 it was originaly the JAC Binyue C20 the Binyue has a controversial design mainly because the rear has a similar design to the Mercedes-Benz C-Class (W203) the car had a 1.8 and a 2.0 liter petrol engines with a 6-speed manual transmission and a 4-speed automatic transmission it was improved in 2011. == Markets == The JAC Binyue was sold mainly in the Chinese market during its entire production run. == Discontinuation == The production of The JAC Binyue ended in 2012 and was replaced by the JAC Refine A60. == References == Category:Chinese automobiles Category:2010s automobiles Category:Sedans
title: JAC Binyue
